quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  76,23,It is We Who send down the Qur’an on you (O Messenger) in parts
  76,24,"So wait patiently for your Lord’s judgment, and pay no heed to (the desires and caprices of) any of them who is a willful sinner or a thankless unbeliever"
  76,25,And remember and mention the Name of your Lord (in worship) in the early morning and in the afternoon
  76,26,"And during part of the night prostrate to Him, and glorify Him a long part of the night"
  76,27,"Those (sinful unbelievers) love and prefer that which is in advance (the present, worldly life), and neglect a grievous Day ahead of them"
  76,28,"It is We Who have created them and made firm their composition, and whenever We will, We can change their structure and character entirely"
  76,29,"All this is an admonition and reminder, and so let him who wills, take a path to his Lord"
  76,30,"You cannot will unless God wills. Surely God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  76,31,"He admits whom He wills into His mercy; and as to the wrongdoers, He has prepared for them a painful punishment"